 <p><center><img src="http://members.aol.com/krungle101/myhomepage/krunglesig.jpg" border=0></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueidolonfaer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eidolon Faer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Dark Lord of Felwithe</span><br>  Posts: 487<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/14/01 11:43:40 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.sprynet.com/~kubik01/eqpics/Sigpic.jpg height=233 width=103></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What I find is quite ironic!</span><hr size=1> Well, I went through the same thing the Original Poster did.  I got 90% of my xp soloing up to level 29 (This was before Kunark, when there was no such thing as Breeze).<br>
<br>
I would get rejected by groups CONSTANTLY.  It was rather disheartening.  'You cannot Nuke' they would say.  'Who needs you?' they would say.<br>
<br>
At level 29 it all turned around, with the gaining of Clarity.<br>
<br>
I had many tanks tell me 'You're just a wussy caster who cannot nuke.  Where the heck do you get off telling me how to fight?'<br>
<br>
After the tanks refused to ASSIST, I started to Charm as a method of Crowd Control.  At least one warrior bitched at me for making a fool out of him.  He fought the Charmed MOB for 2 or 3 full combats in a row.  I told him to ASSIST.  He got rude.<br>
<br>
But then something interesting happened.<br>
<br>
When I offered to leave, the Cleric stood up and told the Warrior to shut the hell up and listen to me.<br>
<br>
It was astonishing how fast the Warrior turned around.<br>
<br>
Of course, once he saw how well the (now standard) tactics worked, he acted like it was his idea all along.  But at least I was not dying from broken Mezzes.<br>
<br>
Clarity was the wedge to get into groups.  When Breeze came along it removed a huge hurdle.  Before Breeze nobody wanted you till 29.  Then you were a god (after 28 levels of abuse).  If you wonder why Enchanters have a reputation for being rude, arrogant, and controlling, remember what we went through on the way up.  And how many times we died from other people not bothering to do things right.<br>
<br>
And if you wonder why Enchanters get along with Clerics, well, the Clerics can make the meleers listen.  NOBODY crosses their healer.<br>
